Royal Taylor Gieves & Hawkes Sells Flagship Store, Times Says

-- B y   A l e x   M o r a l e s
-- 
2011-09-18T07:16:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-18/royal-taylor-gieves-hawkes-sells-flagship-store-times-says.html
Gieves & Hawkes Plc, the U.K.
tailor to clients including Princes William and Harry, sold its
flagship  London  store to a group controlled by parent company
Hong Kong-based  Wing Tai Properties Ltd. (369) , the Sunday Times
 reported , without saying where it obtained the information.  As well as selling the store at 1 Savile Row, London for
8.5 million pounds ($13.4 million), Gieves & Hawkes closed eight
concessions, including seven at House of Fraser stores, the
newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Morales in London at 
 amorales2@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at   landberg@bloomberg.net . 